@startuml
title BP-01 - Tenant Onboarding and School Activation

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  DiamondBackgroundColor White
  DiamondBorderColor Black
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
}

|Super Admin|
start
:Receive school onboarding request;
:Review school identity and administrative data;

if (School data complete?) then (Yes)
  :Create tenant record;
  :Assign unique tenant code;
  :Set tenant status to INACTIVE;
else (No)
  :Request missing or corrected information;
  stop
endif

|Platform|
:Create isolated tenant context;
:Prepare default tenant configuration;
:Prepare default roles and access scope;

note right
Business rules:
- Every school is an independent tenant.
- Financial data must be isolated by tenant.
- Initial access uses UserTenantRole.
- Inactive tenants cannot run financial operations.
end note

|Super Admin|
:Create initial School Administrator account;
:Assign SCHOOL_ADMIN role to the tenant;

|School Administrator|
:Receive account activation instructions;
:Log in to the platform;
:Review school profile and financial configuration;

if (Configuration valid?) then (Yes)
  :Confirm school setup;
else (No)
  :Update school profile and configuration;
  :Confirm school setup;
endif

|Super Admin|
:Activate tenant;

|Platform|
:Set tenant status to ACTIVE;
:Allow tenant scoped access;
:Record onboarding audit trail;
:Notify School Administrator;

|School Administrator|
:Access active school workspace;
stop
@enduml
